All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
BlockURL
The BlockURL class implements the Command interface and represents a command to block a specific URL in a file by adding it to the end of the file's content.
Command
The Command interface represents a command to be executed.
Console
The Console is the main component in the program, it accepts commands from the user.
CookiesFlag
A class representing the cookies flag.
DownloadFromURL
DownloadFromURL is a class that implements the Command interface, allowing users to download content from a specified URL with various filtering options.
Errors
Class Errors contains the errors in the program (except for error codes).
Flag
An abstract class that represents a flag for a connection, such as "cookies" or "images".
FlagFactory
A factory class that creates Flag objects based on their type.
FlagType
An enum that represents the different types of flags that can be applied to a connection.
FromListFlag
A flag that blocks connections to sites listed in a file.
HTMLFlag
The HTMLFlag class represents the flag for HTML content type.
ImageFlag
The `ImageFlag` class represents a flag that blocks image content.
Main
Java Program - Proxy This is a console-based program to test some proxy-like functions which control the downloading of URL resources from the web.
PrintList
The PrintList class implements the Command interface, used to execute the command of printing the contents of a file to the console.
UnblockURL
The UnblockURL class implements the Command interface and represents a command to unblock a specific URL in a file by removing it from the file's content.
